# GPTOPT NIP STARTER FILE
# Preset: Competitive Latency Baseline
# Status: strategy manifest / not yet validated against a real exported NPI .nip sample

[Profile]
Name=GPTOPT - Competitive Latency Baseline
Intent=Prioritize frametime stability, lower latency, and competitive consistency
Scope=Create as a game-specific profile, not a broad global override

[Targets]
FrameCapStrategy=Use a deliberate external or in-game cap method; do not stack conflicting cap methods blindly
VRRStrategy=Keep intentional and test with the chosen sync path
TextureFilteringQuality=High Performance only if image-quality loss is acceptable and testable
ThreadedOptimization=Auto unless a game-specific test proves otherwise
ShaderCache=Keep enabled unless troubleshooting corruption or stutter behavior
LowLatencyApproach=Prefer the game's own latency path first, then profile-level changes only if justified
PowerManagement=Prefer maximum performance only for the game-specific profile if testing supports it
AnisotropicFiltering=Prefer application-controlled unless a game-specific override is needed
Antialiasing=Prefer application-controlled for competitive presets

[Validation]
Check1=Average FPS
Check2=1 percent low
Check3=Frametime spike behavior
Check4=GPU utilization trend
Check5=Input feel consistency

[Rollback]
Method=Export the original profile first and change one setting bucket at a time
